reviewText: This is one of best animes ever for sure. The battle scenes are worth every penny. This is a must own.

I bought this box set because I have all of the previous box sets of Bleach. This box set was truly awesome, the battle with Aizen got very intense, that was most of the story in this box set. There is at least one weird episode, so be on the lookout. I definitely recommend this box set as long as you have the 20 box sets that came before this one.

I love Bleach.  These box sets are incredible....  BUT....The complete Bleach series is available on Hulu.  They are sub-titled but I was surprised how naturally they flowed, coming from someone who had only watched the dubbed version.  I wish I had known before spending over $500 on box sets.

Sign up for 1 free month and watch them all.  And guess what: it's not just what's been released in the US... it's all 360+ episodes.

5 stars for Bleach and these sets - and I hope this advice helps some of you out there.

This is an example of how I wish the animators and writers for the Bleach filler episodes had done a better job. As much as people hated the Bount Arc way back in the beginning, those filler episodes were written and handled much better than the ones that came after trying to draw out the anime as it caught up with the manga.

Still worth the purchase for Bleach lovers

Ichigo and his dad are right behind him, but they stop so that Ichigo can take some time and talk to Zongetzo and learn the Altamont get zoga tensho. but will this be enough to stop Aizen.
